photo.title: "Monsoon City"

description._content:
This day was epic from start to finish chasing the monsoon Summer light! Here you can see several Bay Area icons including: The Transamerica Pyramid, Alcatraz, Coit Tower, and Mt.Tamalpais. The fog ended up being too much that day and I decided it wouldn't pay off to stick around the Golden Gate Bridge and Marin Headlands, even though it looked good in the beginning, and boy am I glad I followed my gut because the fog just overtook everything down there.

This was taken in downtown San Francisco.

photo.title: Below the Bay Bridge, San Francisco

description._content: California road trip: From the first time I was introduced to this view by the Flickr community, I knew, that next time I found myself in San Francisco, this was going to be a high priority, sunset location. Even despite my research seemingly showing it to be a tricky location to get to. I was pleasantly surprised, that it's not as difficult to get to, as people make out. It's just a short walk from the road, down a well trodden path, where one can easily find a stable piece of land for a tripod. I was, however, grateful I was able to be dropped off, as there is strict parking restrictions on the nearest road. It's also worth noting that the roads that connect Yerba Buena island with civilisation have been recently redeveloped. More recently than the 2010 USA maps I had in my sat nav anyway! 3 exposure bracketed HDR. RAW files blended using Oloneo PhotoEngine and Adobe Photoshop Elements. ---- Thanks for visiting! If you would like to order any prints, please check out my website... www.andygittos.com

description._content:
Well, this was the super moon rise over the Coit tower tonight. I was about at the right spot to see it but did not expect to thees clouds from the east side. It was more clouds / haze before sunset time. I would say that was a totally lucky snapshot. Otherwise I may not see the moon tonight :). 

Enjoy this super moon view. San Francisco is a beautiful  city in all aspects.
